 Since e coequalizes a and b, mfa = gea = geb = mfb, so since
  m is a monomorphism, fa = fb. Now f coequalizes a and
  b, so there is a lift y\to  x which factors f through e. Since e
  is an epi, further this lift factors g through m.

The following are equivalent for a homomorphism G\xrightarrow {f}H of
groups:


f is a monomorphism;

f is injective;

f has trivial kernel.

A subobject classifier in a finitely complete
category is a monomorphism
*\xhookrightarrow {\top } \Omega  such that, for every
subobject s\hookrightarrow  x, there exists a unique map x\xrightarrow {\chi _s} \Omega ,
called the characteristic or classifying map  of the subobject such
that 




